## Point-In-Time Limitations

The smoke pipeline preserves adapter `available_from` timestamps and keeps real
runs bounded by configured `max_days` and `max_records`. It is still a smoke
check, not a full vintage database. Source release calendars, revisions, market
holidays, and provider-specific publication lags require additional validation
before research use.
